## v1.1.0 -> v1.2.0 (2026-06-21)

- **Version:** 1.1.0 -> 1.2.0 (MINOR — adds new findings/failed-attempts, not a rewrite)
- **Date:** 2026-06-21
- **Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus issue #1553 ("Skills missing `argument-hint` frontmatter field") planning
- **Verification level:** verified-local (the evidence re-reads + parse-checks were RUN this session; the PR/CI for #1553 had NOT landed at capture time)
- **What changed:**
  - Generalized the description from cross-repo-only to ANY audit, with explicit emphasis on multi-target audits where a SUBSET is already fixed, the scope-creep discipline (fix only named targets), and the "no test for an unenforced doc/UX field" rule. Added trigger (4) for multi-target partial-staleness.
  - Added a `v1.2.0 note` to the Overview documenting the single-repo, multi-target frontmatter case: `skills/brainstorm/SKILL.md:4` already had `argument-hint` (stale audit), only `python-repo-modernization` was genuinely missing; the field is unenforced so verification is a YAML parse, not a unit test.
  - Added two "When to Use" triggers (multi-target audits; unenforced config/frontmatter fields) and a "Related" cross-reference to `agent-config-validation-and-integrity`.
  - Added Verified Workflow steps 8-11: verify each named target separately; survey the whole population for convention + true scope but fix only named targets; don't invent a test where no contract exists; derive the field value from behavior and place it per convention.
  - Added a multi-target-frontmatter block to Quick Reference (per-target `sed`, population survey `awk`, no-test-contract grep, frontmatter-parse `python3 -c`).
  - Added four Failed Attempts rows (trusting a multi-target audit verbatim -> no-op edit on already-fixed `brainstorm`; expanding the fix to all skills -> scope creep; inventing a unit test for an unenforced field; copying a generic placeholder for the field value).
  - Added a ProjectHephaestus #1553 block to Results & Parameters (named targets + their states, convention, enforcement = none, out-of-scope siblings, provenance taken at face value).
- **Why:**
  - Planning #1553, the issue named TWO skills as missing `argument-hint`, but `skills/brainstorm/SKILL.md:1-6` already had it at line 4 (audit snapshot 2026-06-16 was stale). Trusting the issue verbatim would have planned a no-op edit a reviewer NOGOs. A repo-wide `awk` survey both confirmed `brainstorm` was already compliant and surfaced ~10 other non-compliant skills — deliberately excluded to respect one-issue-per-PR. The field has no test contract (`grep -rl "argument-hint" tests/` empty), so verification is a frontmatter parse, not a unit test. These sharpen the existing skill's core lesson (re-read cited evidence before planning) for the multi-target, single-repo, unenforced-field shape.

